---

# Suraksha.pro — Product Requirements Document (PRD)
**Version:** 1.0 | **Status:** Draft | **Platform:** Web (PWA) + Android | **Last Updated:** May 2026

---

## 1. Executive Summary

Suraksha.pro is a real-time crowd safety platform for large-scale events. It combines live crowd density monitoring, predictive risk detection, and instant multi-channel staff communication into a single unified system — a "crowd control tower" that gives admins full situational awareness, coordinators zone-level control, and stewards simple, actionable instructions, all in real time.

**Tagline:** *"From chaos to command."*
**Core Promise:** 60 seconds of earlier warning is the difference between prevention and tragedy.

---

## 2. Problem Statement

### 2.1 Current Reality

Large events rely on WhatsApp groups for coordination, physical walkie-talkies for communication, security guards' gut instinct for crowd assessment, and reactive responses once danger is already visible.

### 2.2 Root Cause of Crowd Tragedies

**No early warning** — density thresholds are crossed before anyone notices (Astroworld, 2021). **Siloed communication** — security, medics, and command aren't on the same page (Hajj stampedes). **Slow response** — by the time the right person is informed, minutes are lost (Love Parade, 2010).

### 2.3 The Gap

By the time a crowd surge is visible to the human eye, it is already in a dangerous phase. A system that detects abnormal density patterns 60–90 seconds earlier provides a critical intervention window.

---

## 3. Product Vision & Goals

**Vision:** *"A real-time crowd control tower that predicts danger and coordinates response before chaos begins."*

**P0 — Must Have (MVP):** Real-time crowd density monitoring across event zones, automated risk detection with actionable alerts, instant push-to-talk staff communication via WebRTC, admin dashboard with live zone heatmap, steward mobile interface with PIN-based access.

**P1 — Should Have:** Coordinator-level zone assignment and reporting, zone-specific communication channels, risk history log and event analytics, broadcast commands from admin to all staff.

**P2 — Nice to Have:** Historical risk pattern analysis across events, IoT sensor integration, post-event PDF report export.

---

## 4. Target Users & Personas

**Raj — Event Safety Director (Admin).** Age 38. Sits in command van with laptop/tablet. Currently manages 5 WhatsApp groups simultaneously during events. Needs: complete visibility, fast override capability, ability to coordinate all teams. Goal: see every zone, know every risk, talk to anyone instantly.

**Priya — Zone Coordinator.** Age 28. Assigned to Zone B (Entry Gates). Uses smartphone while walking her zone. Gets drowned in mass WhatsApp broadcasts irrelevant to her zone. Needs: zone-specific alerts, ability to report what she sees, clear instructions. Goal: know what's happening in her zone, nothing else.

**Arjun — Ground Steward.** Age 22. Crowd control at Gate 3. Uses basic Android phone, sometimes wearing gloves. Misses instructions in noisy environments. Needs: simple interface, cannot afford to read long messages mid-crowd. Goal: get a clear 1–2 line instruction the moment something changes.

---

## 5. User Roles & Permissions

**Admin (Command Room):** Full dashboard access. Creates and manages events. Sees all zones, risks, alerts. Sends broadcast commands. Manages staff.

**Coordinator (Zone Manager):** Assigned to specific zones. Receives alerts for their zones. Can report ground reality. Views zone-level metrics.

**Steward (On-Ground Staff):** Simple mobile UI. Joins via PIN. Receives instructions. Pushes 1-tap status updates. PTT access to zone channel.

Permission matrix — Create/manage events: Admin only. View full dashboard: Admin only. View own zone dashboard: Admin + Coordinator. Receive alerts: Admin (all zones), Coordinator + Steward (own zone only). Send broadcast commands: Admin only. PTT: All roles. Join via PIN: Coordinator + Steward.

---

## 6. Functional Requirements

### Authentication

FR-AUTH-01: System shall support Email/Password login via Supabase Auth. FR-AUTH-02: System shall support role-based account types — Admin, Coordinator, Steward. FR-AUTH-03: Coordinators and Stewards shall be able to join events via Event PIN without requiring email signup. FR-AUTH-04: Admin account creation requires email verification. FR-AUTH-05: PIN-based sessions shall expire when the event ends or after 24 hours, whichever is earlier.

### Event Management

FR-EVT-01: Admin shall be able to create a new event with name, date, expected capacity, venue zones (A–Z), and per-zone capacity. FR-EVT-02: System shall auto-generate a unique 6-digit Event PIN upon event creation. FR-EVT-03: Admin shall be able to start, pause, and end an event. FR-EVT-04: Only one event per admin can be in "Active" status at a time. FR-EVT-05: Coordinators joining via PIN shall select their assigned zone(s). FR-EVT-06: System prevents duplicate coordinator assignment to the same zone.

### Zone Monitoring

FR-ZON-01: Dashboard shall display all event zones as a live heatmap grid. FR-ZON-02: Each zone shall display current density (people/m²), flow rate (movement speed), risk score (0–100), and active alert count. FR-ZON-03: Zone colors shall update in real time — Green (Safe), Yellow (Building Risk), Red (Critical). FR-ZON-04: Admin shall be able to tap any zone to view its detailed metrics panel. FR-ZON-05: Density and flow data shall refresh at a maximum interval of 5 seconds.

### Risk Detection

FR-RISK-01: System shall compute a Risk Score (0–100) per zone every 5 seconds. FR-RISK-02: System shall detect Surge (sudden density spike >15% in 30s), Bottleneck (high density + near-zero movement), and Stampede Risk (rapid density fluctuation, variance >3σ in 60s). FR-RISK-03: Each detected risk shall output Risk Type, Risk Score, Confidence Level, and a recommended action. FR-RISK-04: Risk history per zone shall be stored and accessible post-event.

### Alert System

FR-ALRT-01: Alerts shall be generated automatically when Risk Score exceeds threshold. FR-ALRT-02: Yellow alert at score ≥ 40; Red alert at score ≥ 70. FR-ALRT-03: Alerts pushed to Admin dashboard feed, Coordinator app (own zone), and Steward app (own zone). FR-ALRT-04: Each alert shall contain zone name, risk type, suggested action, and timestamp. FR-ALRT-05: Admin shall be able to acknowledge and resolve an alert manually. FR-ALRT-06: Unresolved red alerts shall trigger audio and vibration notification.

### Communication (WebRTC)

FR-COM-01: System shall provide push-to-talk (PTT) voice channels via WebRTC. FR-COM-02: Available channels — Global (all staff) and per-zone channels. FR-COM-03: Admin can broadcast to all channels simultaneously. FR-COM-04: Stewards are auto-subscribed to their zone channel and the global channel. FR-COM-05: Active speaker shall be visually indicated in the communication panel. FR-COM-06: Only one user may transmit at a time per channel (half-duplex PTT). FR-COM-07: PTT latency shall not exceed 500ms under normal network conditions.

### Steward Quick Updates

FR-STW-01: Stewards shall have 1-tap status report buttons — 🟢 All Clear, 🟡 Crowd Building, 🔴 Emergency. FR-STW-02: Steward updates shall appear in the admin alert feed with timestamp and zone. FR-STW-03: Steward UI shall require zero text input during active events.

