## 7. Screen-by-Screen Specifications

### Screen 1 — Splash Screen

Shown to all users. Content: Suraksha.pro logo centered, tagline *"Prevent. Don't React."*, subtle animated background (pulsing heatmap motif). Auto-redirects to Auth Page after 2.5 seconds or on tap. Deep maroon background, gold logo. No interactive elements.

### Screen 2 — Landing Page (Website Only)

Shown to unauthenticated visitors. Five sections: (1) Hero — headline, sub-headline, two CTAs: [Create Event] and [Join Event with PIN]. (2) Problem — three reference cards (Astroworld, Hajj, Love Parade), handled respectfully with no imagery. (3) How It Works — three-step flow: Monitor → Detect → Respond. (4) Features strip — Real-time Heatmap, AI Risk Detection, WebRTC Walkie-Talkie. (5) Footer with login/signup links.

### Screen 3 — Auth Page

Three flows. Login: Email + Password fields, [Login] button, link to Sign Up. Signup (Admin only): Name, Email, Password, Confirm Password, role auto-set to Admin, email verification required. PIN Join (Coordinator / Steward): 6-digit PIN entry, role selector, zone selector (appears after PIN validation), [Join Event] button. Validation: invalid PIN shows "Event not found or PIN expired". Duplicate coordinator zone assignment shows warning.

### Screen 4 — Admin Home Dashboard

Four-panel layout on desktop, tab-based on mobile.

**Panel A — Live Zone Map (Primary Focus).** Grid of zone cards. Each card shows zone label, density bar, risk score badge, and color state. Tap to expand Zone Detail Modal.

**Panel B — Metrics Overview.** Total estimated headcount, active alerts count, highest-risk zone highlighted, staff online count.

**Panel C — Alert Feed (Real-Time).** Scrollable chronological feed. Each item shows zone, risk type, recommended action, timestamp, and [Acknowledge] button. Unread alerts pulse. Filter by All / Unresolved / Zone.

**Panel D — Communication Panel.** Channel list (Global, Zone A, Zone B, etc.), active channel indicator, PTT button (large, hold to talk), active speaker name display, Broadcast button (Admin only — pushes to all channels simultaneously).

**Header bar:** Event name + LIVE indicator, active staff count, [End Event] button with confirmation modal.

### Screen 5 — Zone Detail Modal (Admin)

Triggered by tapping a zone card. Shows zone name and current status, live density graph (last 10 minutes), flow rate trend line, risk score arc gauge (0–100), risk type and confidence label, alert history for this zone (last 5 entries), [Talk to Zone] PTT button, and [Send Instruction] text broadcast button.

### Screen 6 — Coordinator App

Three tabs. (1) My Zone: zone name and risk status, density meter, flow rate indicator, latest alert card with recommended action, [Mark All Clear] / [Report Issue] toggle buttons. (2) Communicate: PTT button for zone channel, global channel access, text message input for non-urgent admin updates. (3) Alerts: chronological alert history for own zone, acknowledge button per alert.

### Screen 7 — Steward App

Single screen, no navigation required. Gloves-friendly design principle.

Top section: Zone name and event name in large text. Center: Current instruction card — displays latest instruction from admin/coordinator, minimum 18px font, auto-scrolls if long. Bottom: Three full-width status report buttons — 🟢 ALL CLEAR, 🟡 CROWD BUILDING, 🔴 EMERGENCY (each 72px tall). PTT button: fixed bottom-right FAB, hold to talk. Notification banner: slides down from top on new alert.

### Screen 8 — Create Event (Admin)

Three-step wizard. Step 1 — Event Details: Event Name, Date & Time, Venue Name, Expected Total Capacity. Step 2 — Zone Setup: [+ Add Zone] button, per zone fields for Label (A, B, C…), Zone Name, and Capacity. Minimum 1 zone, maximum 26 zones. Step 3 — Review & Generate: summary card of all zones and capacities, [Create Event] button, success screen showing Event ID and PIN (large, copyable), share PIN option.

### Screen 9 — Event History (Admin)

List of past events with name, date, and duration. Tap to view event summary, peak risk moments timeline, full alert log, and staff activity. P2: export as PDF report.

