## 8. Risk Detection Engine

### Input Data Sources

Manual steward status updates (discrete events, on tap), coordinator reports (on submit), simulated sensor feed for MVP (density and flow, every 5 seconds), historical zone baseline (static, per event setup).

MVP Note: In v1.0, density and flow data will be simulated or manually entered. The architecture is designed to accept real IoT or camera-analytics feeds in future versions.

### Risk Score Formula

```
Risk Score = (0.5 × DensityFactor) + (0.3 × FlowFactor) + (0.2 × VolatilityFactor)

DensityFactor    = (current_density / zone_capacity) × 100
FlowFactor       = inverse(flow_rate_normalized)   // low flow = high risk
VolatilityFactor = stddev(density, last_6_readings) × 10
```

### Pattern Detection Rules

**Surge:** Density increases >15% in 30 seconds → Risk Score +20, Confidence High.
**Bottleneck:** Density >70% capacity AND flow rate <10% baseline → Risk Score +25, Confidence High.
**Stampede Risk:** Density variance >3σ in 60 seconds → Risk Score +35, Confidence Medium.
**Slow Build:** Steady density increase over 5+ minutes → Risk Score +10, Confidence Medium.

### Output Object Per Zone (JSON)

```json
{
  "zone_id": "B",
  "timestamp": "2026-05-05T18:32:00Z",
  "density": 340,
  "capacity": 500,
  "flow_rate": 1.2,
  "risk_score": 74,
  "risk_type": "BOTTLENECK",
  "confidence": "HIGH",
  "recommended_action": "Redirect inflow from Gate 2 immediately. Open overflow corridor C3.",
  "color_state": "RED"
}
```

---

## 9. Alert System

### Alert Lifecycle

```
DETECTED → TRIGGERED → ACKNOWLEDGED → RESOLVED
```

DETECTED: Risk score crosses threshold. TRIGGERED: Alert created in DB, pushed to relevant roles via Supabase Realtime. ACKNOWLEDGED: Admin or Coordinator marks it as seen. RESOLVED: Human confirms situation is controlled OR risk score drops below threshold for 2 consecutive readings.

### Alert Message Template

❌ Weak: *"High risk detected in Zone C."*

✅ Strong: *"Zone C — Bottleneck forming at main entry. Density 68%. Redirect crowd to Gate 4. Close Gate 2 temporarily."*

Template: `[ZONE NAME] — [RISK TYPE] detected. Density at [X]% capacity. [Flow condition]. ACTION: [Specific recommended action].`

### Alert Priority Levels

LOW (score 0–39): Green, no notification. MEDIUM (score 40–69): Yellow, silent push. HIGH (score 70–100): Red, audio + vibration. CRITICAL (score 85–100): Pulsing red, repeated audio + lock screen.

### Alert Routing by Role

MEDIUM: Admin feed only, Coordinator feed only, Steward banner only. HIGH: Admin feed + audio, Coordinator feed + audio + vibration, Steward full-screen banner. CRITICAL: All channels + persistent for Admin and Coordinator, full-screen + lock screen for Steward.

---

## 10. Communication System (WebRTC)

### Channel Structure

```
Global Channel          ← All staff (Admin broadcasts here)
├── Zone A Channel      ← Admin + Zone A Coordinator + Zone A Stewards
├── Zone B Channel      ← Admin + Zone B Coordinator + Zone B Stewards
└── Zone C Channel      ← (and so on)
```

### PTT Mechanics

User holds the PTT button → audio starts transmitting. On release → transmission stops, channel opens for next speaker. If channel is occupied → transmit button shows "Channel Busy" and is non-tappable. Active speaker name and animated audio wave shown to all listeners.

### Technical Requirements

WebRTC peer connections managed via Supabase Realtime signaling. STUN/TURN servers required for devices behind NAT. Fallback: if WebRTC unavailable, show "Voice unavailable — use text alerts." Audio codec: Opus (low-latency, mobile-optimized). Max PTT latency: 500ms target, 1000ms acceptable maximum.

### Text Broadcast (Admin)

Admin can type and send a text message to any channel. Delivered to all members as an in-app notification and alert feed entry. Timestamp and sender role displayed.

---

## 11. Event Management System

### Event States

```
DRAFT → ACTIVE → PAUSED → ENDED
```

DRAFT: Event created, PIN generated, no live monitoring. ACTIVE: Live monitoring on, staff can join, alerts enabled. PAUSED: Monitoring paused (break/intermission), alerts suppressed. ENDED: Read-only, data preserved for review.

### PIN System

6-digit numeric PIN, auto-generated. Unique per event. Valid only while event is ACTIVE or PAUSED. Admin can regenerate PIN at any time (invalidates previous PIN immediately).

### Staff Join Flow

```
Enter PIN → Validate → Select Role → Select Zone → Enter Event
```

PIN validation is real-time via Supabase. Coordinators must select a zone (enforced). Stewards may select a zone or be auto-assigned. System prevents duplicate coordinator assignment to the same zone.

---

## 12. Non-Functional Requirements

**Performance:** Dashboard refresh rate ≤5 seconds. Alert delivery latency ≤2 seconds. PTT voice latency ≤500ms. First contentful paint ≤2 seconds on 4G. Concurrent users per event: up to 200 (MVP).

**Reliability:** System uptime target 99.5% during scheduled events. All alerts and zone logs stored permanently in Supabase. Graceful degradation: if WebRTC fails, text alerts remain fully functional.

**Security:** All API calls require Supabase JWT authentication. Row-Level Security (RLS) enforced — users can only read data from their own event. Event PINs hashed in database, never stored in plaintext. Admin actions logged with timestamps.

**Accessibility:** Minimum font size 16px body, 24px alert text on steward app. Touch targets minimum 48×48px. Color not used as sole indicator — icons accompany all color states. WCAG AA contrast compliance.

---

## 13. Technical Architecture

### System Overview

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   CLIENT LAYER                       │
│   React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS           │
│  ┌────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────┐  │
│  │ Admin PWA  │  │ Coordinator PWA │  │ Steward  │  │
│  │ Dashboard  │  │ Zone App        │  │ Mobile   │  │
│  └────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └──────────┘  │
└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘
                       │
┌──────────────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐
│                SUPABASE BACKEND                      │
│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐  │
│  │   Auth   │  │ Postgres │  │ Realtime (WS)     │  │
│  │  (JWT)   │  │    DB    │  │ Zone updates      │  │
│  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  │ Alert feed        │  │
│                               │ PTT signaling     │  │
│                               └───────────────────┘  │
└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘
                       │
┌──────────────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐
│              WebRTC VOICE LAYER                      │
│  STUN/TURN servers for NAT traversal                 │
│  Signaling via Supabase Realtime channels            │
│  Opus audio codec · Half-duplex PTT                  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Technology Stack

Frontend framework: React 18 + Vite. Language: TypeScript. Styling: Tailwind CSS. Backend: Supabase (Auth, DB, Realtime). Database: PostgreSQL via Supabase. Real-time sync: Supabase Realtime WebSockets. Voice: WebRTC with Opus codec. Mobile: PWA (no app store required). Hosting: Vercel or Netlify.

### Supabase Realtime Channels

`event:{eventId}:zones` — zone density and risk updates → Admin, Coordinators. `event:{eventId}:alerts` — new alert objects → Admin, Coordinators, Stewards. `event:{eventId}:staff` — staff join/leave events → Admin. `zone:{zoneId}:updates` — steward status taps → Admin, Zone Coordinator. `webrtc:{channelId}:signal` — WebRTC offer/answer/ICE → channel members.

