## 15. UI/UX Design System

### Color Palette (Mahabharata Theme)

`--color-bg-primary: #0D0408` — Main app background. `--color-bg-surface: #1A0A10` — Card/panel backgrounds. `--color-bg-elevated: #2A1018` — Modals, dropdowns. `--color-maroon: #7B1C2C` — Primary brand color. `--color-maroon-dark: #4A0F1A` — Hover/pressed states. `--color-gold: #C9A84C` — Accents, icons, headings. `--color-gold-light: #E8C97A` — Highlight text. `--color-text-primary: #F5ECD5` — Body text (warm off-white). `--color-text-secondary: #A08060` — Labels, subtitles. `--color-safe: #2E7D32` — Zone Safe. `--color-warning: #F57F17` — Zone Building Risk. `--color-danger: #C62828` — Zone Critical. `--color-danger-pulse: #FF1744` — Critical alert animation. `--color-border: #3D1A22` — Subtle borders.

### Typography

App Title: Inter/Cinzel, 28px, weight 700. Section Heading: Inter, 20px, weight 600. Card Title: Inter, 16px, weight 600. Body: Inter, 14px, weight 400. Alert Text: Inter, 16px, weight 500. Steward Instructions: Inter, 18px, weight 600. Zone Labels: Inter Mono, 32px, weight 700.

### Component Anatomy

**Zone Card:**
```
┌────────────────────────┐
│  ZONE B                │  ← Gold label
│  ████████░░  68%       │  ← Density bar (color-coded)
│  Flow: 1.2 m/min       │
│  Risk: 74   [HIGH]     │  ← Red badge
└────────────────────────┘
```

**Alert Card:**
```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  🔴 ZONE C — BOTTLENECK                          │
│  Density 68% · Flow rate critical                │
│  ► Redirect crowd to Gate 4. Close Gate 2.       │
│                       18:32:04   [Acknowledge]   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**PTT Button (Steward):** 80px circular button, gold border, microphone icon. Hold state: pulsing red ring + "TRANSMITTING" label. Channel busy: grey disabled + "BUSY" label.

### Motion & Animation

Zone color transitions: 600ms ease-in-out. Critical alert card: 2s pulse animation (border glow). PTT transmitting ring: 1s infinite pulse. New alert slide-in: 300ms from right. Risk score gauge update: 500ms smooth arc.

---

## 16. Android-Specific Requirements

### Display

Always show status bar — do not use fullscreen or immersive mode. Always show navigation bar — Android system buttons must not be hidden. All content rendered within safe area insets. Orientation: portrait-locked for steward app, landscape-capable for admin dashboard.

### Touch Target Sizing

PTT Button: 80×80px minimum. Steward Status Report Buttons: full width × 72px each. Zone Cards (Admin): minimum 120×100px. Navigation Tab Items: 48×48px. Alert Acknowledge button: 44×44px minimum.

### PWA Manifest (Critical)

```json
{
  "name": "Suraksha.pro",
  "short_name": "Suraksha",
  "display": "browser",
  "orientation": "portrait",
  "theme_color": "#7B1C2C",
  "background_color": "#0D0408",
  "start_url": "/"
}
```

**Critical:** `"display": "browser"` is mandatory to keep Android system bars visible. Never use `"standalone"` or `"fullscreen"` — this is a hard requirement.

### Network Resilience

Service Worker caches core app shell for offline load. Network status indicator shown when offline. Steward status updates queued locally and sent on reconnect. PTT shows "No connection — voice unavailable" banner if WebRTC fails.

---

## 17. Demo Flow / Acceptance Scenario

```
T+0:00  Admin creates event "Navaratri 2026"
        Zones: A (Entry), B (Main Stage), C (Food Court), D (Exit)
        Capacity: 500 per zone. Event PIN generated: 847291

T+0:02  Coordinator Priya joins via PIN → assigned Zone B
        4 Stewards join, distributed across all zones

T+0:05  Event goes ACTIVE. All zones GREEN on dashboard.

T+0:15  Zone B crowd builds as concert approaches.
        Density: 210 → 260 → 310 people
        Risk score climbs: 28 → 42 → 58
        Zone B card turns YELLOW.
        Alert: "Zone B — Crowd build detected. Density at 62%."
        Priya's coordinator app shows YELLOW with action guidance.

T+0:18  Zone B density: 370 people. Flow rate drops to near-zero.
        BOTTLENECK pattern detected. Risk score: 74.
        Zone B turns RED. CRITICAL alert fires.
        Audio alert triggers on admin dashboard.
        Stewards in Zone B receive full-screen red banner.

T+0:19  Admin speaks on Zone B PTT channel:
        "Zone B team — open overflow Gate 3 now.
         Redirect queue from Gate 1."
        Priya acknowledges via coordinator app.
        Steward Arjun taps [CROWD BUILDING] status update.

T+0:21  Gate 3 opened. Crowd redistributes.
        Density: 370 → 340 → 300 → 260 (over 2 minutes)
        Flow rate recovers.
        Risk score: 74 → 55 → 38
        Zone B returns to YELLOW, then GREEN.
        Admin resolves the alert manually.

T+0:23  All zones GREEN. Event continues safely.
        Full risk timeline logged to event history.
```

---

## 18. Out of Scope (MVP v1.0)

Physical IoT sensor or camera integration. AI/ML predictive modeling (current engine is rule-based). Native Android/iOS app (PWA only). Multi-event concurrent management by a single admin. Automated emergency services notification. PDF export of post-event reports. Multi-language support. Payment or subscription billing. Event ticketing integration. Facial recognition or biometric features (explicitly excluded for privacy).

---

## 19. Risks & Mitigations

**WebRTC fails on poor network** (Severity: High, Likelihood: Medium) — Mitigation: fallback to text-only mode, show warning banner.

**Supabase Realtime drops connection** (Severity: High, Likelihood: Low) — Mitigation: auto-reconnect logic, offline alert queue with local sync.

**False positive risk alerts** (Severity: Medium, Likelihood: Medium) — Mitigation: configurable thresholds per event, admin can dismiss alerts with one tap.

**Steward PIN shared externally** (Severity: Low, Likelihood: Medium) — Mitigation: PIN rate-limiting, admin can regenerate PIN instantly.

**Admin dashboard flooded with alerts** (Severity: Medium, Likelihood: Medium) — Mitigation: alert deduplication logic, zone-level grouping, "zone mute" option.

**Browser denies microphone for PTT** (Severity: High, Likelihood: Medium) — Mitigation: explicit microphone permission prompt on join, graceful fallback to text.

**Android system bars hidden** (Severity: High, Likelihood: Low) — Mitigation: enforce `"display": "browser"` in PWA manifest, test on target device matrix before launch.

---

## 20. Glossary

**Zone:** A defined physical area of the event venue with its own capacity and monitoring. **Risk Score:** A computed 0–100 value representing crowd danger level in a zone. **Surge:** A sudden spike in crowd density (>15% increase in 30 seconds). **Bottleneck:** High density combined with near-zero crowd movement. **Stampede Risk:** Rapid, oscillating density changes indicating unstable crowd behavior. **PTT:** Push-to-Talk — a voice communication mode where one user transmits at a time. **Event PIN:** A 6-digit code that allows Coordinators and Stewards to join an event. **Flow Rate:** The average movement speed of people within a zone. **Color State:** Visual zone indicator — Green (Safe), Yellow (Building), Red (Critical). **Confidence Level:** How certain the system is about a detected risk pattern — Low, Medium, or High. **PWA:** Progressive Web App — a web app installable on mobile without an app store. **Realtime Channel:** A Supabase WebSocket channel used to push live data to connected clients. **Half-duplex:** Communication where only one party can speak at a time (walkie-talkie style). **STUN/TURN:** Server infrastructure enabling WebRTC connections across firewalls and NAT. **RLS:** Row-Level Security — database policy ensuring users only access their own event data.

